
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `mako-render` baraye ejra va namayeshe template-haye Mako (yek engine template-sazi baraye Python) estefade mishavad. Yani shoma mitavanid yek file template Mako ra bedahid va natijeye an ra be dast آورید.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--template FILE` --> 📄 File template Mako ke bayad render shavad.
    🔹 `--data DATA`     --> 💾 Dadeh-haee ke baraye template estefade mishavad (mitavanad JSON bashad).
    🔹 `--output FILE`   --> 📤 Natijeye render shode ra dar yek file zakhire mikonad.
    🔹 `--module-directory DIR` --> 📁 Pooshe-i baraye zakhire kardane module-haye compiled shode Mako.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ mako-render --template mytemplate.mako

    🔹 Render kardane `mytemplate.mako` va chap kardane natije dar terminal.

    $ mako-render --template mytemplate.mako --data '{"name": "Ali"}'

    🔹 Render kardane `mytemplate.mako` ba dadeh-haee ke dar format JSON dade shode ast.

    $ mako-render --template mytemplate.mako --output output.txt

    🔹 Render kardane `mytemplate.mako` va zakhire kardane natije dar `output.txt`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ mako-render --template hello.mako --data '{"name": "Javad"}'

    🔹 Agar `hello.mako` shamel `Hello, ${name}!` bashad, natije `Hello, Javad!` khahad bood.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `mako-render` command is used to execute and display Mako templates (a templating engine for Python). It allows you to provide a Mako template file and get the rendered output.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--template FILE` --> 📄 The Mako template file to render.
    🔹 `--data DATA`     --> 💾 Data to be used in the template (can be JSON).
    🔹 `--output FILE`   --> 📤 Saves the rendered output to a file.
    🔹 `--module-directory DIR` --> 📁 Directory to store compiled Mako modules.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ mako-render --template mytemplate.mako

    🔹 Renders `mytemplate.mako` and prints the result to the terminal.

    $ mako-render --template mytemplate.mako --data '{"name": "Ali"}'

    🔹 Renders `mytemplate.mako` with the data provided in JSON format.

    $ mako-render --template mytemplate.mako --output output.txt

    🔹 Renders `mytemplate.mako` and saves the result to `output.txt`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ mako-render --template hello.mako --data '{"name": "Javad"}'

    🔹 If `hello.mako` contains `Hello, ${name}!`, the output will be `Hello, Javad!`.
